The paper deals with cooperative localization and synchronization in mobile agent networks, which is a topic closely related to robotics and control (cs.RO) as well as systems and control (cs.SY). The use of Bayesian factor graphs and belief propagation algorithms suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). The consideration of time-varying network connectivity and clock parameters points towards networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
